{
  "stem": "4078.1",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then the next day, my mother wouldn't let me go to school, because I didn't have any clothes.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So she sent me to my grandmother.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My grandmother lived where we used to live, not too far away from where we used to live.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And my mother, by being married to my father, was also prohibited from living in that neighborhood.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "However, because she was British-born, she had special dispensation to go-- I'm not sure if it was once a week or once a month-- to go and visit her mother.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But I, as a child, was allowed to come and go, whenever I wanted.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they had a special identification card, saying that they were aliens.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Which when you think about, it is rather ludicrous, especially for my mother.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "My mother was a, an English lady.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So, anyway.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Then after we were bombed and we had sold our house, they had checked my father and found out that he wasn't a spy, had never been a Nazi, wasn't in cahoots with the Nazis, was Jewish, and obviously wouldn't help the Nazis anyway.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Then they told us, well, you can move back now.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But we didn't--",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I stayed-- yes, I stayed with my grandmother for a week.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then I decided I wanted to be with my parents.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the British government-- I don't know if the government, the local counsel, my mother had gone to the town hall to say that she'd been bombed, and what are you going to do about it, and find me somewhere, and find me some, some clothes.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Everything was rationed.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And all clothing was-- I think they'd started with the clothing coupons in the-- I'm not sure, but anyway.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
